But over and above this, there are other considerations which I do not think ought to be ignored, as bearing upon Mr. Walbran's notiori that Prior Waltheof of Kirkham became successively Abbot of Rievaulx and of Melrose. Mr. Walbran, as already noted (p. xxviii w), states that Prior Waltheof was a kinsman of the Earl of Albemarle, and that it was through his (Waltheof’s) influence that the latter founded the Religious House at Thornton. Assuming that identification to be ascertained, the Mailros Chronicler affords us abundant means of identifying the Abbot of Melrose who was distinguished by the same name.
